26/05/2004
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- The foreign ministers of countries in the Adriatic-Ionian Initiative adopted a resolution Tuesday (25 May) supporting Croatia's EU integration efforts. 
The top diplomats of Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Greece, Italy, Serbia-Montenegro and Slovenia signed the document. 
Slovenian Foreign Minister Dimitrij Rupel, who hosted the forum, said implementing EU standards would bring stability to Southeast Europe. 
(Betanews - 26/05/04; HINA, STA, Onasa - 25/05/04)
